The paper deals with visual question answering (VQA) and specifically focuses on the interpretability of VQA models through visual grounding. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach to training VQA models using automatically obtained supervision, which involves machine learning (cs.AI), optimization (cs.LG), and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. Therefore, these sub-categories are also likely to be relevant to the paper.
